
(for 8 inch square)

topping:
	1 cup flour
	¼ tsp salt
	1 tsp baking powder
	¼ cup melted butter
	½ cup milk
	1 egg (room temp)
	¾ cup honey
filling:
	3 cup fruit
	¼ cup honey
	2 Tbsp butter
	2 Tbsp lemon juice
	½ tsp cinamon
	some tapioca, corn starch and/or arrowroot powder

Oven to 350.
Mix all dry topping ingredients.
Mix wet and add, stirring.

Mix the filling and simmer for 10 minutes.

Pour the filling into 8x8 dish, pour the topping
on top, bake at 350 for ~45 minutes




------------------ recipe 2 -----------------------------------
w/ processed sugar

Preheat oven to 350F

filling:
	tart cherry:
		6 cups cherries
		2/3 cup sugar
		2 Tbsp arrowroot powder
		1/2 tsp vanilla
		1/2 tsp almond extract

	Blend filling ingredients and bring to a low simmer for a few minutes.


topping:
	1 cup flour
	1 cup sugar
	2 tsp baking powder
	1/4 tsp salt
	1/2 tsp cinnamon

	mix dry ingredients, then add

	3/4 cup milk

	and mix until just combined

	Cut 6 Tbsp butter onto bottom of 9x12 baking dish.
	Put dish into oven with butter while pre-heating and
	let the butter soften/melt.  Pour topping into the pan
	and spread into an even layer.  Add the filling, then
	bake ~45 minutes at 350F
